% att/2 Fakten  (Dung 1995 — binär; Typ/conf aus LLM-Kandidaten als Kommentar)
att(pro63b, pro7).  % [undermining] conf=70 — The moral equivalence claim challenges the premise that protecting fetal life justifies proscribing abortion after viability
att(pro27, pro7).  % [undermining] conf=80 — Pro27’s conclusion that the Constitution does not define a fetus as a person attacks the legal premise that the State can protect fetal life after viability.
att(pro71, con152).  % [rebuttal] conf=85 — A claims early abortions are widely accepted, while B’s conclusion to enact a law banning abortions from conception directly contradicts that acceptance
att(con8, pro71).  % [undermining] conf=70 — Claim that fetuses feel pain challenges the premise that early, less‑developed fetuses are morally less concerning.
att(con23, pro63).  % [rebuttal] conf=80 — B’s commitment to ending all abortions implies all abortions are unjustified, directly contradicting A’s claim that not all are unjustified.
att(con152, pro63).  % [rebuttal] conf=75 — Introducing legislation that defines life at conception presumes abortion is unjustified, opposing A’s assertion that some abortions are justified.
att(con23, pro63b).  % [rebuttal] conf=95 — Con23 asserts abortion should be ended, directly contradicting pro63b's claim that abortion is justified.
att(con152, pro63b).  % [rebuttal] conf=90 — Con152 promotes legislation defining life at conception, opposing the justification of abortion.
att(con8, pro63b).  % [undermining] conf=80 — Con8 claims fetuses feel pain, challenging the premise that killing a fetus is analogous to killing an adult.
att(con140b, con152).  % [undermining] conf=80 — If the claim that Anthony and Stanton spoke out against abortion is false, it undermines the premise B uses to justify introducing the Life at Conception Act.
att(con109, con24).  % [undermining] conf=80 — The repeat‑abortion statistic implies many women continue to abort despite any alleged overwhelming guilt, undermining that premise.
att(con109, con24b).  % [undermining] conf=80 — Showing many women have prior abortions suggests that abortions do not universally cause nightmares, thus attacking that premise.
att(con109, con24c).  % [undermining] conf=80 — If many women undergo multiple abortions, it challenges the claim that abortion leads to excessive drinking as a universal outcome.
att(con109, con24d).  % [undermining] conf=80 — The prevalence of repeat abortions undermines the premise that abortion inevitably leads to drug abuse.
att(con109, con24e).  % [undermining] conf=80 — High rates of repeat abortions suggest abortion does not necessarily cause promiscuity, attacking that claim's premise.
att(con109, con24f).  % [undermining] conf=80 — The statistic that many women have prior abortions challenges the assertion that abortion causes an inability to form or maintain relationships.
att(con109, con24g).  % [undermining] conf=80 — Frequent repeat abortions indicate that abortion does not inevitably cause difficulty bonding with later children, undermining that premise.
att(con109b, con24).  % [undermining] conf=80 — Even with 8.5 % of women having three or more abortions, it suggests guilt is not universally overwhelming, undermining that premise.
att(con109b, con24b).  % [undermining] conf=80 — The fact that a notable share of women have multiple abortions challenges the claim that abortions cause nightmares, attacking that premise.
att(con109b, con24e).  % [undermining] conf=60 — If many women undergo several abortions, it weakens the premise that abortion leads to promiscuity, since repeat abortions would be unlikely if that were true.
att(con152, pro71).  % [rebuttal] conf=85 — [symmetric rebuttal] A claims early abortions are widely accepted, while B’s conclusion to enact a law banning abortions from conception directly contradicts that acceptance
att(pro63, con23).  % [rebuttal] conf=80 — [symmetric rebuttal] B’s commitment to ending all abortions implies all abortions are unjustified, directly contradicting A’s claim that not all are unjustified.
att(pro63, con152).  % [rebuttal] conf=75 — [symmetric rebuttal] Introducing legislation that defines life at conception presumes abortion is unjustified, opposing A’s assertion that some abortions are justified.
att(pro63b, con23).  % [rebuttal] conf=95 — [symmetric rebuttal] Con23 asserts abortion should be ended, directly contradicting pro63b's claim that abortion is justified.
